How the Process Works
Going solar with EARE Engineering is a straightforward process. Here is what to expect from start to finish:

1. Free site assessment. We visit your property, look at your roof, check your current electricity usage, and understand what you need from a solar system.
2. Custom proposal. We put together a proposal that shows you exactly what we recommend, what it costs, and what you can expect in terms of savings and backup power.
3. Approval and scheduling. Once you are happy with the proposal, we handle any required paperwork and schedule your installation.
4. Installation day. Our team installs your panels, inverter, batteries and all the electrical connections. Most residential jobs are done in one to two days.
5. Certificate of Compliance. Our registered electricians sign off the installation and issue your COC.
6. Handover. We show you how your system works, how to check your monitoring, and give you our contact details for any future questions or support.

Most residential installations are up and running within two to three weeks from your first enquiry. Larger commercial projects take longer depending on the size of the system.

