Frequently Asked Questions

What is included in a solar installation?
A full installation from EARE Engineering includes solar panels, an inverter, battery storage, all wiring and electrical connections, a Certificate of Compliance, and a handover showing you how to use and monitor your system. We handle everything in-house.

Will my solar system keep the power on during load shedding?
Yes, as long as you have battery storage included in your system. When the grid goes off, your batteries supply power to your home or business. The size of your batteries determines how long you can run and which appliances you can use during an outage.

How long does installation take?
Most residential installations take one to two days on site. From your first enquiry to a fully working system, you are usually looking at two to three weeks. This depends on equipment availability and your property. Larger commercial jobs take longer.

Do I need permission from the municipality to install solar?
It depends on your municipality and the size of your system. For most residential installations in the Western Cape, the requirements are manageable. We handle all the necessary paperwork and applications on your behalf so you do not have to worry about it.

What is a Certificate of Compliance (COC)?
A COC is a document issued by a registered electrician that confirms your electrical installation meets the required safety standards. It is important for your insurance and for the safety of everyone in the building. Every installation we do includes a COC.

Can I start with just a battery backup and add solar panels later?
Yes. We design our systems with expansion in mind. If you want to start with a battery backup system and add solar panels later, we will make sure the initial installation is set up in a way that makes the upgrade simple and affordable.

How much does solar installation cost in the Western Cape?
A basic battery backup system starts from around R25,000. A mid-size residential solar system with battery storage typically falls between R100,000 and R180,000. Commercial systems vary widely depending on size. The only accurate way to get a price is through a site assessment, which we offer for free.

What areas do you cover?
We cover Somerset West, Strand, Gordon's Bay, Stellenbosch, Franschhoek, Paarl, Grabouw and Cape Town. Our main base is in Somerset West, so our response times in the Helderberg area are especially fast.

Do you also do electrical and air conditioning work?
Yes. EARE Engineering offers electrical installations and maintenance, air conditioning installation and servicing, and solar installation all under one roof. Many of our clients use us for all three services.

